---
/**
 * consensus-deep-dive · Figure 1 — the HERO "consensus contract" banner.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/distributed-systems/consensus-deep-dive.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). It lives as an .astro component, NOT inline in the
 * MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG that uses
 * kebab-case attributes (text-anchor, font-size, stroke-width, marker-end, …).
 *
 * The source page declared its arrowhead markers (#arw / #arwA / #arwG) ONCE in a
 * hidden top-of-body <svg defs>. Because each figure is now an isolated component,
 * the #arwA marker this figure references via marker-end="url(#arwA)" is inlined
 * here in a local <defs> so it resolves standalone (verbatim from the source defs).
 */
---

<figure style="margin-top:1.6rem">
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 240"
        role="img"
        aria-label="The consensus contract: agreement, validity, termination — FLP says you cannot guarantee all three deterministically in an asynchronous system with one crash"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arwA"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#7a1f12"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="320"
                y="24"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110"
                >THE CONSENSUS CONTRACT — three properties one protocol must keep</text
            >
            <!-- three property cards -->
            <rect
                x="20"
                y="46"
                width="186"
                height="74"
                rx="9"
                fill="#eef5ee"
                stroke="#2f5d3a"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="113"
                y="68"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="13"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">AGREEMENT</text
            >
            <text x="113" y="86" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#6b675f"
                >no two correct nodes</text
            >
            <text x="113" y="100" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#6b675f"
                >decide differently</text
            >
            <rect
                x="227"
                y="46"
                width="186"
                height="74"
                rx="9"
                fill="#eef5ee"
                stroke="#2f5d3a"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="320"
                y="68"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="13"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">VALIDITY</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="86" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#6b675f"
                >a decided value</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="100" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#6b675f"
                >was actually proposed</text
            >
            <rect
                x="434"
                y="46"
                width="186"
                height="74"
                rx="9"
                fill="#f7ecea"
                stroke="#9a2417"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="527"
                y="68"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="13"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">TERMINATION</text
            >
            <text x="527" y="86" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#6b675f"
                >every correct node</text
            >
            <text x="527" y="100" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#6b675f"
                >eventually decides</text
            >
            <!-- FLP verdict -->
            <rect x="60" y="150" width="520" height="40" rx="10" fill="#1c1b18"></rect>
            <text
                x="320"
                y="168"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#e8b3a6">FLP (1985): you cannot guarantee all three —</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="183" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" fill="#f3efe3"
                >deterministically, in a purely asynchronous system, if even one node may crash.</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="214" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >Safety (the two green ones) is always kept. Termination is the one that gives way.</text
            >
            <text x="527" y="138" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#9a2417"
                >↑ this is the casualty</text
            >
            <line x1="527" y1="142" x2="527" y2="122" stroke="#9a2417" marker-end="url(#arwA)"
            ></line>
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Memorise this banner. Every level below either proves <em>why</em> termination must yield, or
        shows how a real protocol keeps the two safety properties anyway.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
